Deborah-Digges:
I see that the pull request is for changes to a .md file. Could this be the reason that it is not triggering notifications to you? I also see that your .metion-bot blacklists .md files
. This is happening because the algorithm is returning an empty list of reviewers for this particular PR. You can try it using the API:
mentionBot.guessOwnersForPullRequest("https://github.com/bunto/mention-bot", 3, "SuriyaaKudoIsc", "master", {}, github)
.then(function(users) {   
    console.log(users);
})
.catch(function(err) {
console.error(err);
});
You will see an empty list. If the list is empty, the code skips this particular pull request.
To avoid this, set the configuration for 
{"alwaysNotifyForPaths": [
  {
       "name": "ghuser", // The user's Github username
       "files": ["*.*"] // The array of file globs associated with the user
    }
]}
in .mention-bot to avoid the list ever being empty
. No, this was something I ran in the node console just to see what's going on. Replace ghuser with the name of the default user for all pull requests.
